# CODEOWNERS — auto-improve
#
# A single maintainer owns this repo, so the rule is simple: every change
# requests a review from @crimeacs. GitHub auto-adds the matching owner as a
# reviewer when a PR touches the paths below. Precedence is by file order —
# the last matching pattern wins — so the area-level lines below take effect
# over the catch-all above them.
#
# Syntax: https://docs.github.com/articles/about-code-owners

# Catch-all — everything in the repo is owned by the maintainer.
*                       @crimeacs

# The loop itself — the apply ladder, the pairwise gate, the climb.
# Treat changes here as load-bearing.
/improve.py             @crimeacs
/requirements.txt       @crimeacs

# Rubrics — the specs auto-improve optimizes against.
/criteria/              @crimeacs

# Bundled runnable examples.
/examples/              @crimeacs

# Live climb chart (Rust / macroquad).
/plot/                  @crimeacs

# Spoken-delivery variant (ElevenLabs, audio-model judge).
/voice/                 @crimeacs

# Repo governance and CI.
/.github/               @crimeacs
